main event: A witness observed a round drifting object in the sky for over 4 minutes in Wichita, Kansas.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at 10,000 feet and moved at a low speed without making any noise or leaving a trail,The sighting began at a 15-degree elevation and disappeared from view at a 20-degree elevation beyond a garage roof,The object appeared very large when viewed through a seven times binoculars,The witness was Mrs. Dewey who reported the object drifting slowly in a south east direction,The conclusion of the report suggests that the object was likely a balloon.
witness description: Mrs. Dewey, who observed the object using binoculars
